Description: This is a great playing and awesome looking Epiphone Les Paul Custom with a killer pair of humbuckers! Thie guitar featurea a double-bound body, bound fingerboard with pearloid block inlays, a slimtaper “D” profile neck and great sounding alnico classic humbuckers. Simply put, this guitar offers a great look, feel and sound all at an affordable price!This guitar is 14 years old and has been sitting in a closet for almost all that time. It's in excellent shape... but that's not to say it couldn't benefit from a setup.Body: Solid, double-bound mahogany body in black finish. Stop-Bar Tailpiece and Tune-O-Matic bridge. Speed control knobs and a 4-ply black pickguard, still with original plastic wrap.Neck: Slim taper D-profile mahogany neck with a bound rosewood fingerboard. Pearloid block inlays and a 1 11/16” nut. Bound headstock with Grover tuners, 24 ¾” scale length.Pickups/Electronics: Epiphone Alnico Classic humbuckers in the neck and bridge with dual volume and tone controls and a 3-way selector switch.Case: Includes an unoriginal plastic molded hardshell case.
Title: Epiphone Les Paul Custom
